| Source | Lines | Units | % of Total |
|---|---|---|---|
| `style_dna_analogue` (Tier 4) | 63,408 | 76,904 | **79.8%** |
| `minimum_presentation` (Tier 5) | 19,155 | 19,490 | **20.2%** |
| `store_historical` (Tier 1) | 0 | 0 | 0% |
| `cluster_average` (Tier 2) | 0 | 0 | 0% |
| `grade_average` (Tier 3) | 0 | 0 | 0% |

> [!NOTE]
> **Why is Tier 1-3 at 0%?** The demand engine's Tier 1-3 matches on exact `sku_id` (store × specific SKU ROS). Since SS26 styles are brand-new, there's zero sales history for these exact SKUs. The system correctly fell back to **Style DNA** (finding similar styles from SS25 sales) and **minimum presentation** quantities. This is the intended cold-start behavior.

